title: Unemployment rate in the Bahamas 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Unemployment rate has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Unemployment rate, about 16.18 was reported at Year 2013
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 6.87 was reported at Year 2001
